    @MediaClass(uuid1=218169601,

            uuid3=4352,

            description="The SourceClip class represents the essence and identifies the source of the essence.",

public class SourceClipImpl
extends SourceReferenceSegmentImpl
implements SourceClip, QSourceClip, Serializable, Cloneable

    Implements a representation of essence and identifies the source of the essence. This interface uses the source reference values to manage the properties of a source clip.

    See Also:
    TypeDefinitions.SourceClipStrongReference, Serialized Form

        Creates and initializes a new source clip, which represents an item of essence and identifies the source of the essence.

        Parameters:
        dataDefinition - Kind of data represented by this component.
        length - Length of the source clip component.
        sourceReference - Reference to the source clip.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - The data definition and/or source reference arguments are null.
        BadLengthException - The length of the component must be non-negative.

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                throws PropertyNotPresentException
        Description copied from interface: SourceClip

        Returns the position offset from the origin of the referenced package's track in edit units determined by the source clip's context. If the source package identifier of this value is the zero package id, then the start position shall also be set to 0.

        Specified by:
        getStartPosition in interface SourceClip
        Returns:
        Position offset from the origin of the referenced content.
        Throws:
        PropertyNotPresentException - The optional start time property is not present, indicating that the reference is in the context of a static track rather than a timeline track or event track.

      • setStartPosition

        @MediaPropertySetter(value="StartPosition")
public void setStartPosition(Long startPosition)
        Description copied from interface: SourceClip

        Sets the position offset from the origin of the referenced package's track in edit units determined by the source clip's context. If the source package identifier of this value is the zero package id, then the start position shall also be set to 0. Set this optional property to null to omit it.

        Specified by:
        setStartPosition in interface SourceClip
        Parameters:
        startPosition - Position offset from the origin of the referenced content.
